subject: meta-fii/meta-kudo: Add Ampere Altra (MAX) SSIF IPMI driver
commitMessage:
meta-fii/meta-kudo: Add Ampere Altra (MAX) SSIF IPMI driver

1. Add Ampere SSIF IPMI driver to provide the interface
between CPU & BMC
2. Add Ampere SSIF IPMI drover supports Nuvoton chipset

Tested-by:
1. Load image on the Nuvoton RunBMC CRB
2. Use ipmitool to test the command under BMC console
  a. ipmitool mc info
  b. ipmitool sdr
  c. ipmitool lan print
  d. ipmitool channel info 1
  e. ipmitool user list 1
  f. ipmitool chassis status
  g. ipmitool raw 0x06 0x01
  h. ipmitool power status

Signed-off-by: Lancelot Kao <lancelot.kao@fii-usa.com>
Signed-off-by: Mohaimen alsmarai <Mohaimen.alsamarai@fii-na.com>
Change-Id: I4789863f4d1394919d653aee3e52597dd9094f9b

Patch Set 15:

Hi Lancelot,
The ssifbridge code is already upstreamed at https://github.com/openbmc/ssifbridge so you don't need to add the code again in your repo. And the bitbake recipe is put at https://github.com/openbmc/openbmc/blob/master/meta-phosphor/recipes-phosphor/ipmi/phosphor-ipmi-ssif.bb.
You can just add below in your machine conf file:
PREFERRED_PROVIDER_virtual/obmc-host-ipmi-hw = "phosphor-ipmi-ssif"
